  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate if percutaneous drainage of sterile fluid
      collections recurring after initial aspiration in acute pancreatitis yielded better results
      than their conservative management.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
